This paper is related to intrusion detection and prediction, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also uses recurrent neural networks (RNNs) for modeling, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves semantic modeling of system-calls, which is related to natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI) (cs.AI). The use of RNNs also falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves building a prediction model for system behavior, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE).
